[1] UK (Bedforshire)
Date: Fri 19 Jul 2013
Source: Bedford Today [edited]
http://www.bedfordtoday.co.uk/news/today-s-choice/measles-cases-in-central-beds-1-5299546


Public health figures revealed this week that there have been 6 cases of measles in Central Beds between January and May [2013] -- compared to zero in Bedford and Luton. The figures were released by Public Health England to encourage parents to make sure their child has been vaccinated against the highly-infectious disease.

"Thanks to the hard work of local health teams we are making good progress towards the 95 per cent target, but there still remains a large number of 10-16 year olds, together with many younger children and adults who are under-vaccinated. The programme will continue until we reach as many children as possible in the age groups most affected. If your child has not had 2 doses of the MMR [measles, mumps, rubella] vaccine, the upcoming summer holiday is a good time to contact your GP."

Director of public health Muriel Scot said: "We're actively working across all schools to promote the importance of the MMR Programme and have written to schools to raise awareness and to increase uptake. The local programme in Bedfordshire for all 10-16 year olds runs via local GPs so we are encouraging all parents to make an appointment for their child to have a free vaccination."

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail from HealthMap Alerts
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Bedfordshire is a central county of England, bordering the counties of Cambridgeshire to the north-east, Northamptonshire to the north, Buckinghamshire to the west, and Hertfordshire to the south-east. It can be located in the map of the counties of England at: http://www.itraveluk.co.uk/maps/england/. - Mod.CP

