[4] Spain (Mallorca, Balearic Islands)
Date: Fri 19 Jul 2013
Source: Diario de Mallorca [in Spanish, trans. Mod.JT, edited]
http://www.diariodemallorca.es/mallorca/2013/07/19/salud-confirma-brote-12-casos/861410.html

Measles outbreak in Mallorca
----------------------------
The Regional Ministry of Health confirmed yesterday [18 Jul 2013] that there was an outbreak of up to 12 cases of measles in a kindergarten in Palma in the 20th week of this year (approximately over the month of May) [2013]. The same sources said that the Directorate General of Health Public acted immediately, following established protocols for these cases, and that the source of infection could stop there without new infections being detected. Also, the Department of Health said that parents are counseled to take the children who had contact with the patients to the doctor and to get vaccinated.

Finally, Public Health said that so far this year [2013] there have been 36 cases of measles in the [Balearic] islands.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-ESP
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Mallorca is an island located in the Mediterranean Sea. It is the largest island in the Balearic Islands archipelago in Spain. The capital of the island, Palma, is also the capital of the autonomous community of the Balearic Islands. The Cabrera Archipelago is administratively grouped with Mallorca (in the municipality of Palma). The island can be located in the map of Spain at: http://spain.europemaps.info/. - Mod.CP

