[6] Pakistan (Rawalpindi, Punjab)
Date: Sun 21 Jul 2013
Source: Pakistan Today [edited]
http://www.pakistantoday.com.pk/2013/07/20/city/islamabad/measles-cases-rise/


A total of 10 more measles cases have been reported in the Holy Family Hospital (HFH) Rawalpindi [Punjab province], while a general rise in measles cases have been witnessed throughout the city. Approximately, 634 measles affected children were brought to HFH, out of whom 435 were admitted and kept in isolation wards. However, only 10 children now remain and are under treatment in the hospital. According to the physician in charge of the Infectious and Disease Ward, Dr Javed Hayat, the recovery period spans up to 14 days but takes longer if the patient is already suffering from another infection.

Doctors claimed that children already vaccinated against measles are not risk-free but their complications are mild compared to those who have not been vaccinated. Dr Hayat advised the parents to get their children vaccinated [in a timely manner] to reduce the risk of complication from the disease.

--
