[7] Canada (Quebec)
Date: Mon 15 Jul 2013
Source: 98,5 fm Montreal [in French, trans. Mod.CP, edited]
http://www.985fm.ca/regional/nouvelles/un-cas-de-rougeole-repertorie-a-gatineau-252829.html


The health authorities of the Gatineau-Ottawa are asking physicians to be alert to detect any new cases of measles in their patients. A child in Gatineau [Quebec province] had to be treated at the Children's Hospital of Eastern Ontario last week for this viral infection. Some 50 people who have been in contact with the patient have all [been] notified, but the infection could spread further. Symptoms of measles are fever, cough and white spots in the mouth. The virus is transmitted by direct contact with secretions from the nose or throat, especially during coughing and sneezing.

--
